;;Polonska-Vasylenko, Section: Evolution of Ukrainian lands in the 15th-16th centuries; Grand Duchy of Lithuania were transferred to the Polish Crown, while in reality it continued well into the 19th century as the enserfed peasantry and huge estates were left in the Russian and Austria-Hungary|Austrian Empires under the control of the Magnate#Magnates in Poland|Polish magnates, or the Polonized ones, virtually indistinguishable from the former. 

